AI Hackathon Solution Prompts V1.1

# AI Ascent Hackathon — Solution Design

## Step 1: Build an AI Case Library
- Create a structured dataset (one row per case) capturing all key fields:
  - Case ID(auto gen),Owner Login, Job Level, Program/Team, Use Case Title, Problem Statement, AI Technique Used, Tools/Services, Key Prompts, Input Data, Output/Outcome, Performance Metrics (e.g. time saved, accuracy, cost reduction), Status, Date (auto gen), rank (auto gen)
- Source cases from existing AI initiatives, POCs, and production deployments
- Normalize field values for consistent filtering and analysis

## Step 2: Build a Learner Input Portal for AI Initiatives
- Provide a form/interface for learners to submit their own AI initiatives with the same key fields as the Case Library
- Include validation rules to ensure data quality (required fields, dropdown selections for categorical fields)
- Support draft/save/submit workflow so entries can be refined before final submission

## Step 3: Build a Filterable UI to Browse Initiatives
- Display all submitted initiatives in a searchable, sortable table/grid view
- Support filtering by every field (Program, AI Technique, Status, Performance Metrics, etc.)
- Allow export to CSV for offline analysis

## Step 4: Build an Analytics Dashboard
- Visualize initiative data with charts and summaries:
  - By Program/Team: count of initiatives, distribution of AI techniques
  - By Performance: time saved, accuracy improvements, cost reductions
  - By Status: pipeline view (ideation → POC → production)
  - Trend analysis: submissions over time
- Use interactive charts with drill-down capability

## Step 5: Build a Ranking Mechanism
- Score and rank initiatives based on weighted performance criteria:
  - Impact (e.g. time saved, cost reduction, accuracy gain)
  - Scalability (reusability across teams/programs)
  - Complexity vs. effort
  - Innovation factor
- Display leaderboard view with configurable weights
- Allow comparison of top-ranked initiatives side by side

## Step 6: Build an AI Solution Design Agent
- Accept a user-described scenario/problem as input
- Search the AI Case Library for similar cases using semantic matching
- Generate a recommended AI automation solution design including:
  - Suggested AI technique(s) and tools/services
  - Reference cases from the library
  - Estimated effort and expected outcomes
  - Implementation steps
- Allow iterative refinement through follow-up questions
